prvtServicesMIB.name: prvtServicesMIB

revisions.description: Added prefix prvt to Services' traps.
Changed svcVPLSUplinkTable. Corrected various descriptions. Corrected types for some HQOS objects.
Returned for backward compatibility svcMtu; Clarified few attributes descripton.

Lots of changes: 1. Index for the service table is changed. 2. Few objects from the service tables are moved in sdp 3. svcVCId is have now more generic usage. so it's name is changed to svcVPNId 4. The descriptions for some objects are enhanced
Fixed the range of the svcMtu object and changed the description of svcRowStatus.

prvtServicesMIB.contactinfo: BATM/Telco Systems Support team Email: For North America: techsupport@telco.com For North Europe: support@batm.de, info@batm.de For the rest of the world: techsupport@telco.com
prvtServicesMIB.description: This document is the SNMP MIB module to manage and provision the various services of the T-Metro system.

ServiceAdminStatus.name: ServiceAdminStatus
ServiceAdminStatus.description: ServiceAdminStatus data type is an enumerated integer that describes the values used to identify the administrative state of a service.

ServiceOperStatus.name: ServiceOperStatus
ServiceOperStatus.description: ServiceOperStatus data type is an enumerated integer that describes the values used to identify the current operational state of a service.

ServObjName.name: ServObjName
ServObjName.description: ASCII string used to name various service objects.

ServObjDesc.name: ServObjDesc
ServObjDesc.description: ASCII string used to describe various service objects.

ServType.name: ServType
ServType.description: This textual convention is used to specify the type of a given service.

VpnId.name: VpnId
VpnId.description: A number used to identify a VPN. In general each service corresponds to a single VPN, but under some circumstances a VPN may be composed of multiple services.

SdpIdType.name: SdpIdType
SdpIdType.description: A 16-bit number used to identify a Service Distribution Point. This ID must be unique only within the ESR where it is defined. The value 0 is used as the null ID.

TMEncapVal.name: TMEncapVal
TMEncapVal.description: A valid Vlan ID in the range 1-4093, or 65535.

TSapEgrQueueId.name: TSapEgrQueueId
TSapEgrQueueId.description: The value used to uniquely identify a SAP egress queue. The actual valid values are those defined in the given SAP egress QoS policy.

TSapIngQueueId.name: TSapIngQueueId
TSapIngQueueId.description: The value used to uniquely identify a SAP ingress queue. The actual valid values are those defined in the given SAP ingress QoS policy.

custNumEntries.name: custNumEntries
custNumEntries.description: The current number of customer records configured in this device.

custInfoTable.name: custInfoTable
custInfoTable.description: A table that contains customer information.

custRowStatus.name: custRowStatus
custRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this row.

custContact.name: custContact
custContact.description: The name of the primary contact person for this customer.

custPhone.name: custPhone
custPhone.description: The phone/pager number used to reach the primary contact person.

custLastMgmtChange.name: custLastMgmtChange
custLastMgmtChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time of the most recent management-initiated change to this customer.

custMultiServiceSiteEntry.name: custMultiServiceSiteEntry
custMultiServiceSiteEntry.description: Information about a specific customer's multi-service site.

custMultSvcSiteDescription.name: custMultSvcSiteDescription
custMultSvcSiteDescription.description: Generic information about this customer's Multi-Service Site.

custMultSvcSiteIngressSchedulerPolicy.name: custMultSvcSiteIngressSchedulerPolicy
custMultSvcSiteIngressSchedulerPolicy.description: The ingress QoS scheduler policy assigned to this Multi-Service Site.

custMultSvcSiteEgressSchedulerPolicy.name: custMultSvcSiteEgressSchedulerPolicy
custMultSvcSiteEgressSchedulerPolicy.description: The egress QoS scheduler policy assigned to this Multi-Service Site.

custMultSvcSiteLastMgmtChange.name: custMultSvcSiteLastMgmtChange
custMultSvcSiteLastMgmtChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time of the most recent management-initiated change to this multi-service site.

custMultiSvcSiteIngQosSchedStatsTable.name: custMultiSvcSiteIngQosSchedStatsTable
custMultiSvcSiteIngQosSchedStatsTable.description: A table that contains ingress QoS scheduler statistics for the customer multi service site.

custMultiSvcSiteIngQosSchedStatsEntry.name: custMultiSvcSiteIngQosSchedStatsEntry
custMultiSvcSiteIngQosSchedStatsEntry.description: Ingress statistics about a specific customer multi service site ingress scheduler.

custIngQosSchedName.name: custIngQosSchedName
custIngQosSchedName.description: The index of the ingress QoS scheduler of this customer multi service site.

custIngQosSchedStatsForwardedPackets.name: custIngQosSchedStatsForwardedPackets
custIngQosSchedStatsForwardedPackets.description: The number of forwarded packets, as determined by the customer multi service site ingress scheduler policy.

custIngQosSchedStatsForwardedOctets.name: custIngQosSchedStatsForwardedOctets
custIngQosSchedStatsForwardedOctets.description: The number of forwarded octets, as determined by the customer multi service site ingress scheduler policy.

custMultiSvcSiteEgrQosSchedStatsTable.name: custMultiSvcSiteEgrQosSchedStatsTable
custMultiSvcSiteEgrQosSchedStatsTable.description: A table that contains egress QoS scheduler statistics for the customer multi service site.

custMultiSvcSiteEgrQosSchedStatsEntry.name: custMultiSvcSiteEgrQosSchedStatsEntry
custMultiSvcSiteEgrQosSchedStatsEntry.description: Egress statistics about a specific customer multi service site egress scheduler.

custEgrQosSchedName.name: custEgrQosSchedName
custEgrQosSchedName.description: The index of the egress QoS scheduler of this customer multi service site.

custEgrQosSchedStatsForwardedPackets.name: custEgrQosSchedStatsForwardedPackets
custEgrQosSchedStatsForwardedPackets.description: The number of forwarded packets, as determined by the customer multi service site egress scheduler policy.

custEgrQosSchedStatsForwardedOctets.name: custEgrQosSchedStatsForwardedOctets
custEgrQosSchedStatsForwardedOctets.description: The number of forwarded octets, as determined by the customer multi service site egress scheduler policy.

custIngQosPortIdSchedStatsTable.name: custIngQosPortIdSchedStatsTable
custIngQosPortIdSchedStatsTable.description: The custIngQosPortIdSchedStatsTable contains ingress QoS scheduler statistics for the customer multi service site.

custIngQosPortIdSchedStatsEntry.name: custIngQosPortIdSchedStatsEntry
custIngQosPortIdSchedStatsEntry.description: Each entry represents the ingress statistics about a specific customer multi service site ingress scheduler. Entries are created when a scheduler policy is applied to an MSS.

custIngQosPortIdSchedName.name: custIngQosPortIdSchedName
custIngQosPortIdSchedName.description: The value of custIngQosPortIdSchedName is used as an index of the ingress QoS scheduler of this customer multi service site.

custIngQosAssignmentPortId.name: custIngQosAssignmentPortId
custIngQosAssignmentPortId.description: The value of custIngQosAssignmentPortId is used as an index of the ingress QoS scheduler of this customer multi service site. When an MSS assignment is an aps/ccag/lag in 'link' mode, each member-port of the aps/ccag/lag has its own scheduler. This object refers to the portId of these member-ports.

custIngQosPortSchedFwdPkts.name: custIngQosPortSchedFwdPkts
custIngQosPortSchedFwdPkts.description: The value of custIngQosPortSchedStatsFwdPkts represents the number of forwarded packets, as determined by the customer multi service site ingress scheduler policy.

custIngQosPortSchedFwdOctets.name: custIngQosPortSchedFwdOctets
custIngQosPortSchedFwdOctets.description: The value of custIngQosPortSchedStatsFwdOctets represents the number of forwarded octets, as determined by the customer multi service site ingress scheduler policy.

custEgrQosPortIdSchedStatsTable.name: custEgrQosPortIdSchedStatsTable
custEgrQosPortIdSchedStatsTable.description: The custEgrQosPortIdSchedStatsTable contains egress QoS scheduler statistics for the customer multi service site.

custEgrQosPortIdSchedStatsEntry.name: custEgrQosPortIdSchedStatsEntry
custEgrQosPortIdSchedStatsEntry.description: Each row entry represents the egress statistics for a customer multi-service-site egress scheduler. Entries are created when a scheduler policy is applied to an MSS.

custEgrQosPortIdSchedName.name: custEgrQosPortIdSchedName
custEgrQosPortIdSchedName.description: The value of custEgrQosPortIdSchedName is used as an index of the egress QoS scheduler of this customer multi service site.

custEgrQosAssignmentPortId.name: custEgrQosAssignmentPortId
custEgrQosAssignmentPortId.description: The value of custEgrQosAssignmentPortId is used as an index of the egress QoS scheduler of this customer multi service site. When an MSS assignment is an aps/ccag/lag in 'link' mode, each member-port of the aps/ccag/lag has its own scheduler. This object refers to the portId of these member-ports.

custEgrQosPortSchedFwdPkts.name: custEgrQosPortSchedFwdPkts
custEgrQosPortSchedFwdPkts.description: The value of custEgrQosPortSchedStatsFwdPkts represents the number of forwarded packets, as determined by the customer multi service site egress scheduler policy.

custEgrQosPortSchedFwdOctets.name: custEgrQosPortSchedFwdOctets
custEgrQosPortSchedFwdOctets.description: The value of custEgrQosPortSchedStatsFwdOctets represents the number of forwarded octets, as determined by the customer multi service site egress scheduler policy.

prvtCustCreated.name: prvtCustCreated
prvtCustCreated.description: This trap is sent when a new row is created in the custInfoTable.

prvtCustDeleted.name: prvtCustDeleted
prvtCustDeleted.description: This trap is sent when an existing row is deleted from the custInfoTable.

svcNumEntries.name: svcNumEntries
svcNumEntries.description: The current number of services configured on this node.

svcBaseInfoTable.name: svcBaseInfoTable
svcBaseInfoTable.description: A table that contains basic service information.

svcBaseInfoEntry.name: svcBaseInfoEntry
svcBaseInfoEntry.description: Basic information about a specific service.

svcVpnId.name: svcVpnId
svcVpnId.description: This object specifies the ID used by Service Provider(SP). It will have different format according to the type of service. This filed is mandatory. If all mandatory fields are set, the row status object is automatically changed from notReady(3) to notInService(2) state

svcRowStatus.name: svcRowStatus
svcRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this row. The values supported during a set operation are createAndWait(5), destroy(6), active(1), notInSertvice(2). Service can be deleted any time. The transition between svcRowStatus active(1) and notInService(2) states are rejected if svcAdminStatus is up(1).

svcType.name: svcType
svcType.description: The service type: e.g. EtherPipe, TLS, etc. Currently only vpls-pe(11), vpls-mtu(12), vpws-pe(9) and vpws-mtu(10) types are supported. This field is mandatory. Note: For VPLS service, vpls-mtu is supported only.

svcAdminStatus.name: svcAdminStatus
svcAdminStatus.description: The desired state of this service. 1. The transition from down(2) state to up(1) state can be done only if svcRowStatus is either active(1) or notInSercvice(2). 2. The transition from up(1) to down(2) state has to be done in order to modify svcRowStatus object.

svcOperStatus.name: svcOperStatus
svcOperStatus.description: The operating state of this service.

svcNumSaps.name: svcNumSaps
svcNumSaps.description: The number of SAPs defined on this service.

svcNumSdps.name: svcNumSdps
svcNumSdps.description: The number of SDPs bound to this service.

svcLastMgmtChange.name: svcLastMgmtChange
svcLastMgmtChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time of the most recent management-initiated change to this service.

svcLastStatusChange.name: svcLastStatusChange
svcLastStatusChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time of the most recent operating status change to his service.

svcEnableSecureSaps.name: svcEnableSecureSaps
svcEnableSecureSaps.description: Used to configure the SAPs to forward only traffic from the uplink ports.

svcCustName.name: svcCustName
svcCustName.description: The name of the customer this service belongs to.

svcRevertTimer.name: svcRevertTimer
svcRevertTimer.description: Delay before switching to primary pseudowire in seconds

svcVplsMode.name: svcVplsMode
svcVplsMode.description: This object is used to configure whether VPLS operates in qualified or unqualified mode. Qualified and unqualified are not supported, when having per port qualified/unqualified.

svcVPLSUplinkTable.name: svcVPLSUplinkTable
svcVPLSUplinkTable.description: A table that contains information about the VPLS uplink ports.

svcVPLSUplinkIfIndex.name: svcVPLSUplinkIfIndex
svcVPLSUplinkIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the uplink port.

svcVPLSUplinkNetworkPolicy.name: svcVPLSUplinkNetworkPolicy
svcVPLSUplinkNetworkPolicy.description: The network scheduler policy applied to the port.

svcVPLSUplinkNetworkQueueEgressPolicy.name: svcVPLSUplinkNetworkQueueEgressPolicy
svcVPLSUplinkNetworkQueueEgressPolicy.description: The network egress queue applied to the port.

svcVPLSUplinkShaperProfile.name: svcVPLSUplinkShaperProfile
svcVPLSUplinkShaperProfile.description: The ID of the shaping profile applied to the port. 0 indicates no shaping profile.

prvtSvcCreated.name: prvtSvcCreated
prvtSvcCreated.description: This trap is sent when a new row is created in the svcBaseInfoTable.

prvtSvcDeleted.name: prvtSvcDeleted
prvtSvcDeleted.description: This trap is sent when an existing row is deleted from the svcBaseInfoTable.

prvtSvcStatusChanged.name: prvtSvcStatusChanged
prvtSvcStatusChanged.description: The scvStatusChanged notification is generated when there is a change in the administrative or operating status of a service.

sapNumEntries.name: sapNumEntries
sapNumEntries.description: The current number of SAPs configured in this device.

sapBaseInfoTable.name: sapBaseInfoTable
sapBaseInfoTable.description: A table that contains basic SAP information.

sapPortId.name: sapPortId
sapPortId.description: The ID of the access port where this SAP is defined.

sapEncapValue.name: sapEncapValue
sapEncapValue.description: The value of the label used to identify this SAP on the access port specified by sapPortId.

sapRowStatus.name: sapRowStatus
sapRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this row. The values supported during a set operation are createAndGo(4) active(1), notInService(2) and destroy(6). Saps can be deleted any time. The transition between svcRowStatus active(1) and notInService(2) states are rejected if sapAdminStatus is up(1).

sapType.name: sapType
sapType.description: This object indicates the type of service where this SAP is defined.

sapAdminStatus.name: sapAdminStatus
sapAdminStatus.description: The desired state of this SAP. 1. The value of this object depends on the value of svcAdminStatus for the service this sap belongs to. If the sap is created and its service has svcAdminStatus set to down(2), its own admin status will be down(2), otherwise sapAdminStatus will be up(1). 2. If sapRowStatus is in notInService state, the sapAdminStatus transition from down(2) to up(1) state will automaticaly change the value of the sapRowStatus object to active(1)

sapOperStatus.name: sapOperStatus
sapOperStatus.description: The operating state of this SAP, showing also the reason for the current operation state Values ingressQosMismatch(3), egressQosMismatch(4), svcAdminDown(5) and portMtuTooSmall(6) are not supported

sapLastMgmtChange.name: sapLastMgmtChange
sapLastMgmtChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time of the most recent management-initiated change to this SAP.

sapOperFlags.name: sapOperFlags
sapOperFlags.description: This object specifies all the conditions that affect the operating status of this SAP.

sapCustMultSvcSiteName.name: sapCustMultSvcSiteName
sapCustMultSvcSiteName.description: The value of this object, when not null, indicates the Multi-Service Site this SAP is a member of. This information is used to configure the ingress and egress QoS schedulers for this SAP.

sapIngressQosPolicyId.name: sapIngressQosPolicyId
sapIngressQosPolicyId.description: The row index in the hqosSapIngressTable corresponding to this ingress QoS policy, or zero if no policy is specified.

sapEgressQosPolicyId.name: sapEgressQosPolicyId
sapEgressQosPolicyId.description: The row index in the hqosSapEgressTable corresponding to this egress QoS policy, or zero if no policy is specified.

sapIngressQosSchedulerPolicy.name: sapIngressQosSchedulerPolicy
sapIngressQosSchedulerPolicy.description: This object can be set only when sapCustMultSvcSite is null. It indicates the ingress QoS scheduler for this SAP.

sapEgressQosSchedulerPolicy.name: sapEgressQosSchedulerPolicy
sapEgressQosSchedulerPolicy.description: This object can be set only when sapCustMultSvcSite is null. It indicates the egress QoS scheduler for this SAP.

sapLearnMode.name: sapLearnMode
sapLearnMode.description: Sap learning mode. Currently supported as read-only.

prvtSapCreated.name: prvtSapCreated
prvtSapCreated.description: This trap is sent when a new row is created in the sapBaseInfoTable.

prvtSapDeleted.name: prvtSapDeleted
prvtSapDeleted.description: This trap is sent when an existing row is deleted from the sapBaseInfoTable.

prvtSapStatusChanged.name: prvtSapStatusChanged
prvtSapStatusChanged.description: The sapStatusChanged notification is generated when there is a change in the administrative or operating status of an SAP.

sapIngQosQueueStatsOfferedHiPrioPackets.name: sapIngQosQueueStatsOfferedHiPrioPackets

sapIngQosQueueStatsOfferedHiPrioOctets.name: sapIngQosQueueStatsOfferedHiPrioOctets

sapIngQosQueueStatsOfferedLoPrioOctets.name: sapIngQosQueueStatsOfferedLoPrioOctets
sapIngQosQueueStatsOfferedLoPrioOctets.description: The number of low priority octets, as determined by the SAP ingress QoS policy, offered by the service queue.

sapIngQosQueueStatsForwardedInProfPacket.name: sapIngQosQueueStatsForwardedInProfPackets
sapIngQosQueueStatsForwardedInProfPacket.description: The number of in-profile packets (rate below CIR) forwarded by the ingress service queue.

sapIngQosQueueStatsForwardedOutProfPacke.name: sapIngQosQueueStatsForwardedOutProfPackets

sapIngQosQueueStatsForwardedInProfOctets.name: sapIngQosQueueStatsForwardedInProfOctets
sapIngQosQueueStatsForwardedInProfOctets.description: The number of in-profile octets (rate below CIR) forwarded by the ingress service queue.

sapIngQosQueueStatsForwardedOutProfOctet.name: sapIngQosQueueStatsForwardedOutProfOctets
sapIngQosQueueStatsForwardedOutProfOctet.description: The number of out-of-profile octets (rate above CIR) forwarded by the ingress service queue.

sapIngQosQueueStatsDroppedOctets.name: sapIngQosQueueStatsDroppedOctets
sapIngQosQueueStatsDroppedOctets.description: The number of octets discarded in the egress queue.

sapIngQosQueueStatsDroppedPackets.name: sapIngQosQueueStatsDroppedPackets
sapIngQosQueueStatsDroppedPackets.description: The number of in-profile packets discarded by the Ingess queue.

sapIngQosCustName.name: sapIngQosCustName
sapIngQosCustName.description: The Customer Name of the site this SAP belongs to.

sapEgrQosQueueStatsTable.name: sapEgrQosQueueStatsTable
sapEgrQosQueueStatsTable.description: A table that contains egress QoS queue SAP statistics.

sapEgrQosQueueStatsEntry.name: sapEgrQosQueueStatsEntry
sapEgrQosQueueStatsEntry.description: Egress statistics about a specific SAP's QoS queue.

sapEgrQosQueueId.name: sapEgrQosQueueId
sapEgrQosQueueId.description: The index of the egress QoS queue of this SAP.

sapEgrQosQueueStatsForwardedInProfPacket.name: sapEgrQosQueueStatsForwardedInProfPackets
sapEgrQosQueueStatsForwardedInProfPacket.description: The number of in-profile packets (rate below CIR) forwarded by the egress queue.

sapEgrQosQueueStatsForwardedOutProfPacke.name: sapEgrQosQueueStatsForwardedOutProfPackets
sapEgrQosQueueStatsForwardedOutProfPacke.description: The number of out-of-profile packets (rate above CIR) forwarded by the egress queue.

sapEgrQosQueueStatsForwardedInProfOctets.name: sapEgrQosQueueStatsForwardedInProfOctets
sapEgrQosQueueStatsForwardedInProfOctets.description: The number of in-profile octets (rate below CIR) forwarded by the egress queue.

sapEgrQosQueueStatsForwardedOutProfOctet.name: sapEgrQosQueueStatsForwardedOutProfOctets
sapEgrQosQueueStatsForwardedOutProfOctet.description: The number of out-of-profile octets (rate above CIR) forwarded by the egress queue.

sapEgrQosQueueStatsDroppedOctets.name: sapEgrQosQueueStatsDroppedOctets
sapEgrQosQueueStatsDroppedOctets.description: The number of octets discarded in the egress queue.

sapEgrQosQueueStatsDroppedPackets.name: sapEgrQosQueueStatsDroppedPackets
sapEgrQosQueueStatsDroppedPackets.description: The number of in-profile packets discarded by the egress queue.

sapEgrQosCustName.name: sapEgrQosCustName
sapEgrQosCustName.description: The Customer Name of the site this SAP belongs to.

sapIngQosSchedStatsTable.name: sapIngQosSchedStatsTable
sapIngQosSchedStatsTable.description: A table that contains ingress QoS queue SAP statistics.

sapIngQosSchedStatsEntry.name: sapIngQosSchedStatsEntry
sapIngQosSchedStatsEntry.description: Ingress statistics about a specific SAP's QoS queue.

sapIngQosSchedName.name: sapIngQosSchedName
sapIngQosSchedName.description: The index of the ingress QoS scheduler of this SAP.

sapIngQosSchedStatsForwardedPackets.name: sapIngQosSchedStatsForwardedPackets
sapIngQosSchedStatsForwardedPackets.description: The number of forwarded packets, as determined by the SAP ingress scheduler policy, offered by the Pchip to the Qchip.

sapIngQosSchedStatsForwardedOctets.name: sapIngQosSchedStatsForwardedOctets
sapIngQosSchedStatsForwardedOctets.description: The number of forwarded octets, as determined by the SAP ingress schduler policy, offered by the Pchip to the Qchip.

sapIngQosSchedCustName.name: sapIngQosSchedCustName
sapIngQosSchedCustName.description: The Customer Name of the site this SAP belongs to.

sapEgrQosSchedStatsTable.name: sapEgrQosSchedStatsTable
sapEgrQosSchedStatsTable.description: A table that contains ingress QoS queue SAP statistics.

sapEgrQosSchedStatsEntry.name: sapEgrQosSchedStatsEntry
sapEgrQosSchedStatsEntry.description: Egress statistics about a specific SAP's QoS queue.

sapEgrQosSchedName.name: sapEgrQosSchedName
sapEgrQosSchedName.description: The index of the egress QoS scheduler of this SAP.

sapEgrQosSchedStatsForwardedPackets.name: sapEgrQosSchedStatsForwardedPackets
sapEgrQosSchedStatsForwardedPackets.description: The number of forwarded packets by the egress Qchip, as determined by the SAP egress scheduler policy.

sapEgrQosSchedStatsForwardedOctets.name: sapEgrQosSchedStatsForwardedOctets
sapEgrQosSchedStatsForwardedOctets.description: The number of forwarded octets by the egress Qchip, as determined by the SAP egress scheduler policy.

sapEgrQosSchedCustName.name: sapEgrQosSchedCustName
sapEgrQosSchedCustName.description: The Customer Name of the site this SAP belongs to.

sdpNumEntries.name: sdpNumEntries
sdpNumEntries.description: The current number of SDPs configured in this device.

sdpNextFreeId.name: sdpNextFreeId
sdpNextFreeId.description: The next available value for sdpId.

sdpInfoTable.name: sdpInfoTable
sdpInfoTable.description: A table that contains SDP information.

sdpRowStatus.name: sdpRowStatus
sdpRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this row. 1. The values supported during a set operation are createAndWait(5), destroy(6), active(1), notInSertvice(2). Sdps can be deleted any time. The transition between active(1) and notInService(2) states are rejected if sdpAdminStatus is up(1).

sdpDelivery.name: sdpDelivery
sdpDelivery.description: This object specifies the type of delivery used by this SDP. NOTE! Currently we support only mpls. The modification of this obect will be rejected.

sdpFarEndIpAddress.name: sdpFarEndIpAddress
sdpFarEndIpAddress.description: This object specifies the IP address of the remote end of the GRE or MPLS tunnel defined by this SDP. This field is mandatory. If all mandatory fields are set, the row status object is automatically changed from notReady(3) to notInService(2) state.

sdpLabelSignaling.name: sdpLabelSignaling
sdpLabelSignaling.description: This object specifies the signaling protocol used to obtain the ingress and egress labels used in frames transmitted and received on this SDP. When the value of this object is none(1) then the labels are manually assigned at the time the SDP is configured. The value of this object can only be changed while the admin status of the SDP is down(2). This field is mandatory. If all mandatory fields are set, the row status object is automatically changed from notReady(3) to notInService(2) state

sdpAdminStatus.name: sdpAdminStatus
sdpAdminStatus.description: The desired state of this SDP. 1. The value of this object depends on the value of svcAdminStatus. It will be rejected to set sdpAdminStatus to up(1), when svcAdminStatus is set to down(2). 2. If sdpRowStatus is in notInService state, the transition of sdpAdminStatus from down(2) to up(1) state will also automaticaly change the value of the sdpRowStatus object to active(1)

sdpOperStatus.name: sdpOperStatus
sdpOperStatus.description: The operating state of this SDP. 1. Sdp is up and running. 2. Initial state. Entry is inactive. 3. Peers are ready to select transport. 4. There is no suitable transport. 5. SDP is not operational due to local/remote SAP down or remote SDP has no transport. 6. Sdp is up and ready to carry user traffic but it is not used at the moment (backup).

sdpLastMgmtChange.name: sdpLastMgmtChange
sdpLastMgmtChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time of the most recent management-initiated change to this SDP.

sdpLdpEnabled.name: sdpLdpEnabled
sdpLdpEnabled.description: When the value of this object is true(1) the transport LSP's are signalled by LDP, as opposed to being provisioned static or RSVP-signalled LSP's. This object applies only to MPLS SDP's.

sdpOperFlags.name: sdpOperFlags
sdpOperFlags.description: This object specifies all the conditions that affect the operating status of this SDP.

sdpLastStatusChange.name: sdpLastStatusChange
sdpLastStatusChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time of the most recent operating status change to this SDP.

sdpAdminIngressLabel.name: sdpAdminIngressLabel
sdpAdminIngressLabel.description: The static MPLS VC label used by the far-end device to send packets to this device in this service via this SDP.

sdpAdminEgressLabel.name: sdpAdminEgressLabel
sdpAdminEgressLabel.description: The static MPLS VC label used by this device to send packets to the far-end device in this service via this SDP.

sdpAdminIsBackup.name: sdpAdminIsBackup
sdpAdminIsBackup.description: This object is used in administratively to specify the preferred primary or backup state of this SDP. A value of false means this is the primary SDP. This field is mandatory if svcType is set to vpls-mtu(12) or vpws-mtu(10). The sdpType must be set to spoke(2). If all mandatory fields are set, the row status object is automatically changed from notReady(3) to notInService(2) state.

sdpOperIsBackup.name: sdpOperIsBackup
sdpOperIsBackup.description: It represents the current operational state of this SDP as either active or backup. A value of false means this is the active SDP. A value of true means that this SDP is in backup suppressed state.

sdpOutInterface.name: sdpOutInterface
sdpOutInterface.description: This object is valid only if the type of service is tls(3). The ifIndex of the desired outbound interface for this SDP. This field is currently not supported. Its modification will be rejected. The default value is 0

sdpGroupIdentifier.name: sdpGroupIdentifier
sdpGroupIdentifier.description: This object is valid only if the type of service is tls(3). The Group ID for this SDP. SDP's bound to the same service must have the same Group ID's.

sdpTransportTunnelName.name: sdpTransportTunnelName
sdpTransportTunnelName.description: Optional transport tunnel name. For the SDP to be operational an entry must exist in mplsTunnelTable with this name.

sdpType.name: sdpType
sdpType.description: The type of this SDP. Currently the only supported sdp types are spoke(2) and mesh(3) This field is mandatory. If svcType is set to vpls-mtu(12) or vpws-mtu(10), trying to set sdpType to mesh(3) will be rejected(Wring configuration). If all mandatory fields are set, the row status object is automatically changed from notReady(3) to notInService(2) state.

sdpMtu.name: sdpMtu
sdpMtu.description: The largest frame size (in octets) that this SDP can handle

sdpIsPwStatusSignalingEnable.name: sdpIsPwStatusSignalingEnable
sdpIsPwStatusSignalingEnable.description: Specifies if PW-status signalling is enabled per given SDP.

sdpEpsAdminIsPrimary.name: sdpEpsAdminIsPrimary
sdpEpsAdminIsPrimary.description: Administrative primary status if the specified SDP. If set to true, the SDP is the primary-link of the protection.

sdpEpsAdminIsSecondary.name: sdpEpsAdminIsSecondary
sdpEpsAdminIsSecondary.description: Administrative secondary status if the specified SDP. If set to true, the SDP is the secondary-link of the protection.

prvtSdpCreated.name: prvtSdpCreated
prvtSdpCreated.description: This trap is sent when a new row is created in the sdpInfoTable.

prvtSdpDeleted.name: prvtSdpDeleted
prvtSdpDeleted.description: This trap is sent when an existing row is deleted from the sdpInfoTable.

prvtSdpStatusChanged.name: prvtSdpStatusChanged
prvtSdpStatusChanged.description: The sdpStatusChanged notification is generated when there is a change in the administrative or operating status of an SDP.
